03/04/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Former Macedonian Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski pleaded not guilty at the UN war crimes tribunal Friday (1 April). 
He is charged with three counts of violations of the laws and customs of war in connection with a police operation in the ethnic Albanian village of Ljuboten in August 2001. 
Several civilians were killed during the raid. 
Boskovski represented himself at the hearing and said he was committed to defending his honour. 
(Dnevnik - 02/04/05; Reuters, BBC, A1 TV - 01/04/05)
